About that time, Edward, Bishop of Orkney, who was then in Aberdeen for the purpose of favouring the cause of learning, dedicated, with the usual ceremony and much solemnity, the College church (of which mention was made above). He was a man who, by reason of his learning and holy life, had been raised to the highest honou'rs. He was the loving patron of all learned men, as is clearly proved by his uniform kindness to all such in Aberdeen.
